Set up a device IO operation.
Usage: simctl io <device> <operation> <arguments>

Common arguments:
	    --display    Specifies which display to record. Accepts:
	                 - Screen ID (eg: "2")
	                 - Screen name (eg: "TVOut")
	                 - Screen uniqueId (eg: "PurpleTVOut")
	                 - Port UUID (eg: "D5293DAA-4D8C-453E-B049-969FE81936A0"
	                 - Alias (for compatibility): "internal" or "external"
	                 Use 'simctl io <device> enumerate' to list available screens and their IDs.

Supported operations:
	enumerate [--poll]
	    Lists all available IO ports and descriptor states.
	    --poll       Poll after enumeration.

	poll
	    Polls all available IO ports for events.

	recordVideo [--codec=<codec>] [--display=<display>] [--mask=<policy>] [--force] <file or url>
	    Records the display to a QuickTime movie at the specified file or url.
	    --codec      Specifies the codec type: "h264" or "hevc". Default is "hevc".

	    --mask       For non-rectangular displays, handle the mask by policy:
	                 ignored: The mask is ignored and the unmasked framebuffer is saved.
	                 alpha: Not supported, but retained for compatibility; the mask is rendered black.
	                 black: The mask is rendered black.

	    --force      Force the output file to be written to, even if the file already exists.

	simctl writes 'Recording started' to stderr once the first video frame has been processed. Look for this
	if you want to wait for the recording to start.
	Send SIGINT (Control + C) to stop recording. simctl exits once the in-flight frames are processed
	and the video file is finalized.

	screenshot [--type=<type>] [--display=<display>] [--mask=<policy>] <file or url>
	    Saves a screenshot as a PNG to the specified file or url(use "-" for stdout).
	    --type       Can be "png", "tiff", "bmp", "gif", "jpeg". Default is png.

	    --mask       For non-rectangular displays, handle the mask by policy:
	                 ignored: The mask is ignored and the unmasked framebuffer is saved.
	                 alpha: The mask is used as premultiplied alpha.
	                 black: The mask is rendered black.

	screenConfig [--display=<display>] <subcommand> [arguments]
	    Manage device screen configuration.

	    power <on|off>
	        Set the power state of a screen.

	    geometry <width>x<height>[@<scale>]
	        Change the geometry of a screen.
	        The width and height must be compatible with the screen's current mode.
	        If @<scale> is specified, a mode with that scale factor will be selected.

Example:
	Save a screenshot of the booted device to screenshot.png:
	simctl io booted screenshot screenshot.png
